							 	<li><p>
							 		The line passing through <m>P=(3, -1,4)</m> and <m>Q=(1,0,-1)</m>.</p>
							 		<p>
									<!-- <hint>
									</hint> -->
									<solution>
										<p>Our line can be described by <m>\vec{x} = \vect{OP} + t\vect{PQ}</m> since this makes sure that, for <m>t=0</m>, our line passes through <m>P</m>, and for <m>t=1</m>, it passes through <m>Q</m>. The vector equation is therefore given by</p>
									 	<p><me>
									 		\vec{x}
